	     Johannesburg – A 42-year-old taxi driver was arrested and charged with murder, after he allegedly stabbed a fellow taxi driver to death at the Faraday taxi rank in Johannesburg over the weekend, police said on Monday. Police Captain Xoli Mbele said the incident happened at the corner of Grahamstown and Von Wielligh streets in Johannesburg around 16:00 on Sunday afternoon. ALSO READ: Two killed in taxi route dispute Mbele said the taxi driver had allegedly pulled out a knife and stabbed the 38-year-old man in the upper body following an argument. He was declared dead on the scene. ALSO READ: Uber and meter taxi feud claims life of driver The man is expected to appear in the Johannesburg Magistrate’s Court on Monday.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  